entry.title: 3.11 Video Notes
entry.summary: 3.11 Video Notes Learning Objective For binary search algorithims Determine the number of iterations required to find a value in a data set. Explain the requirements necessary to complete a binary search. The binary search algorithm starts at the middle of a sorted data set of numbers and eliminates half of the data; this process repeats until the desired value is found or all elements have been eliminated. Data must be in sorted order to use the binary search algorithm A binary search is often more efficient than sequential/linear search when applied to sorted data.
